A Head Full of Dreams is the seventh studio album by British rock band Coldplay. It is the second album by the band in North America under Atlantic, after Coldplay were transferred from Capitol Records America in 2013.

For various songs on the album, Coldplay collaborated with BeyoncÃ©, Noel Gallagher, Tove Lo and Merry Clayton. The album was produced by Rik Simpson and Stargate. Coldplay have also revealed that the album features a sample of the U.S. President Barack Obama singing Amazing Grace at Clementa C. Pinckney's funeral .
